President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of three directors-general/chief executive officers of three agencies under the Ministry of Mines and Steel Development. This was disclosed in a statement signed by the permanent secretary (general services) in the office of the Secretary to the government of the federation, Olusegun A. Adekunle Esq.
The appointments are National Steel Raw Materials Exploration Agency (NSRMEA) Kaduna, Engr. Umar Albarka Hassan as director-general/CEO; National Metallurgical Development Centre Jos, Prof. (Engr.) Linus Okon Asuquo as director-general/CEO; and Nigeria Institute of Mining and Geosciences Jos, Prof. (Engr.) Suleiman Bolaji Hassan as director-general/CEO. All the appointments are for an initial period of four years, with effect from July 12, 2018.
According to the statement “Mr. President enjoined the new appointees to use their expertise and varied experiences to reposition and reinvigorate the agencies.”